UID:mats-autumn-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260612T001910Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260607
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260608
SUMMARY:Deadline: MATS Autumn 2026 (ML Alignment & Theory Scholars)
DESCRIPTION:MATS (ML Alignment & Theory Scholars) is a research fellowship 
 connecting fellows with mentors from organisations such as Anthropic\, Ope
 nAI\, Google DeepMind\, Redwood Research and ARC to work on reducing front
 ier AI risk. The Autumn 2026 cohort runs for 10 weeks in Berkeley and Lond
 on (28 Sep - 4 Dec 2026)\, with the option to apply for a 6-12 month funde
 d extension. Fellows receive a $12\,500 stipend\, $20\,000 in compute\, fr
 ee housing and meals\, covered travel and J1 visa support\, research manag
 ement\, and a community of peers. SEVEN TRACKS: Empirical\, Theory\, Strat
 egy & Forecasting\, Policy & Governance\, Systems Security\, Founding & Fi
 eld-Building (new)\, and Biosecurity (new)\; applicants may apply to one o
 r more. PROCESS: Stage 1 general application (1-2 hrs\, due June 7)\; Stag
 e 2 central evaluations (early-late June\, e.g. technical/research-taste a
 ssessments for Empirical\, a writing/analytical assessment for Policy & Go
 vernance)\; Stage 3 stream applications with stream-specific questions and
  possible interviews/work tests (June-late July)\; offers late July/early 
 August via a two-sided matching process. ELIGIBILITY: open to researchers 
 and field-builders internationally (travel and J1 visa covered). Applicati
 ons close 7 June 2026 (EOD AOE).\n\nOrganisation: MATS (ML Alignment & The
 ory Scholars)\nLocation: Berkeley\, CA\, USA and London\, UK (in person)\n
 Award: $12\,500 stipend plus $20\,000 compute\, free housing and food\, co
 vered travel and J1 visa (if needed). Option to apply for a 6-12 month fun
 ded extension. No application fee.\nDuration: 10-week program\, 28 Septemb
 er - 4 December 2026 (optional 6-12 month funded extension)\n\nMore: https
 ://www.matsprogram.org/
URL:https://www.matsprogram.org/
LOCATION:Berkeley\, CA\, USA and London\, UK (in person)
END:VEVENT
